      • getNeighbor

        protected java.util.Optional<TileUID> getNeighbor​(java.lang.Boolean physical,
                                                  Direction direction)
        Give the neightbor in a given direction, return an empty Optional if the tile has nothing on that direction
        Parameters:
        physical - True for physical, False for logical
        direction - Direction of the asked tile
        Returns:
        Optional is required in case the query is for a logical neighbor and there are none or for any query and the Tile is on the edge of the map

      • getDirection

        protected java.util.List<TileUID> getDirection​(java.lang.Boolean physical,
                                               Direction direction)
        Get all cells in a given direction, including the current cell, until the neighbor of the last cell does not exist anymore
        Parameters:
        direction - Direction of the asked tiles
        physical - True to pass through walls, False to only follow traversable links
        Returns:
        The Collection is ordered from closest (always the current cell) to farthest
